To edit a filter while viewing a report in Lightning Experience: Run Reports

Apply a field-to-field filter to your report that compares values between fields.
Click Add filter....
Select a field.
Set Operator to less than, Type to Field, and Value to another field.
Click Apply.
Click Save.

Get the Most out of Field-To-Field Filters Tips, Limits, and Limitations
Each report supports up to 4 field-to-field filters.
Field-to-field filters only support these field types: Date, Datetime, Numeric.
Field-to-field filters are unavailable in report types that reference an external object or have a "with or without" relationship between objects.
title: Using Field-to-Field Filters in Salesforce Reports
